This paper deals with workload management for cloud databases, which is a core topic in the field of database systems (cs.DB). The paper proposes a learning-based framework for generating workload management solutions, which involves supervised learning techniques (cs.LG). The paper also discusses resource provisioning and query scheduling, which are topics in distributed computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the adaptation of the offline model to stricter/looser performance goals, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper presents experimental results, which involve the analysis of data and the evaluation of performance metrics, which are topics in data science (cs.DS).
